## Description
We use angular 10 with the cli's built-in service worker for a PWA. A new version v2 of the app was published. The built-in service worker is not behaving as expected: _sometimes_, the old version v1 of the app is displayed even when v2 has been loaded previously by the same browser. The following steps illustrate the odd behaviour (although it occurs rather randomly):

- open the app: old version v1 is shown. This is still OK, as it is served up by the SW from its cache (although I would expect that if the user is online and v2 is available, v2 is displayed).
- reload the page: new version v2 is displayed => OK
- close the tab
- open a new tab and browse to the app. Old version v1 is displayed again. Why? At this point, the service worker should have updated its cache and display v2, right?

It seems the service worker does not update its cache, even when a page reload is done. We see this behaviour occurring very randomly. Often the new version is displayed, and sometimes the old version suddenly pops up.

We observed this behaviour in Chrome and Samsung Internet.

## Desired behaviour
Once the new version v2 is loaded by the browser, the old version v1 should never be displayed again.

